s in curriculum, public policy and education-related subjects. It is also for all training and practising teachers who wish to combine a deeper understanding of major curriculum issues with a critical understanding of the ways in which ideologies impact on formal state education, and to consider ways of producing school curricula that are appropriate to the times we live in"--cProvided by publisher.  a41 0aEducationxCurricula. 0aPublic schools.  aLB 1570 M688 2015c1hUAED-Bi0162035176435  aLB 1570 M688 2015wLCc1i0162035176435d1/20/2017e1/20/2017kCHECKEDOUTlFLOOR_2mUAEDUCn2p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu10/29/201401ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n99024950bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/14100251